# 🏛️ MiniArchi – Your AI Architectural Assistant

**MiniArchi** is a sleek, intelligent web app that lets anyone — architects, designers, students, or curious builders — chat with a GPT-4o-powered AI trained to think like a world-class architect. Whether you’re dreaming up a tiny cabin or a mega-structure, MiniArchi is here to inspire, guide, and problem-solve with you.

🌐 [Try it out (coming soon)](https://miniarchi.vercel.app) — No sign-up required.

---

## ✨ What It Does

- 🤖 Ask architectural questions and get instant, thoughtful answers
- 🧠 Explore creative design solutions and technical calculations
- 🏗️ Get help with building layouts, materials, and space planning
- 📐 Speak naturally — the AI is eloquent, thorough, and realistic
- 🌍 Designed to resonate with global users, especially Africans

---

## 🧠 Powered By

- GPT-4o via OpenAI API  
- Custom system prompt to shape the architect’s personality  
- Next.js App Router + React  
- Tailwind CSS + Framer Motion  
- Serverless architecture for low-latency response  

---

## 🛠️ How It Works

This app is built using the modern **Next.js App Router** and streams responses from OpenAI’s GPT-4o using Vercel’s `ai` SDK.

🧠 The AI behaves like a legendary architect, thanks to a carefully crafted personality prompt:
> “You are a professional architect — the best in the world. You speak eloquently, design boldly, explain deeply, and always promote creativity within engineering limits. You communicate accessibly to Africans and the world.”

---

## 📁 Project Structure

MiniArchi/
├── app/ # Next.js App Router
│ ├── page.tsx # Landing page
│ └── api/chat/ # AI chatbot API route
│ └── route.ts
├── components/ # Chat UI and other reusable components
│ └── ChatComponent.tsx
├── public/ # Static assets
├── styles/ # Tailwind & global styles
├── .env.local # API key (not included in repo)
├── README.md
└── next.config.js

